  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Existing law prohibits the State Energy Resources Conservation and Development Commission from certifying a nuclear fission thermal powerplant, except for specified powerplants, and provides that a nuclear fission thermal powerplant, except specified powerplants, is not a permitted land use in California unless certain conditions are met regarding the existence of technology for the construction and operation of nuclear fuel rod processing plants and of demonstrated technology or means for the disposal of high-level nuclear waste, as specified.\n\nThis bill would exempt a nuclear microreactor, as defined, from those provisions."
    }
  ],
